          "author_association": "OWNER",
          "body": "## Summary\n\nThe ship-issue bot, while shipping issues #8/#9/#10/#12 on pd-book-tools, appended an `### Issue #22 — 2026-05-10 17:27 UTC / Closes #22` section to PR #17's body. Issue #22 (\"Child A: test triage-fork.py pointer comment on parent\") was already closed and is unrelated to coverage work. Had the PR been merged as-is, GitHub would have re-processed the `Closes #22` — at minimum signaling the bot wrote bad metadata, at worst re-closing an unrelated issue if it had been reopened in the interim.\n\n## Repro\n\n`gh pr view 17 -R ConcaveTrillion/pd-book-tools --json body --jq .body` (before R4 cleanup at 2026-05-11) showed the orphan section.\n\n## Root cause hypothesis\n\nIn `/workspaces/ocr-container/scripts/ship-issue-success.sh` (or the skill's PR-body-update step), the bot appends a section based on whatever issue number is in env / ISSUE_JSON. If that number is leftover from a prior aborted cycle, or read from a stale .ship-issue-tmp/ file, the bot appends without validating.\n\n## Suggested fix\n\nBefore `gh pr edit $PR_NUM --body \"$NEW_BODY\"`:\n\n1. Validate the issue number belongs to the current repo: `gh issue view $N -R $REPO --json state,number` — must succeed and state must be OPEN.\n2. If state is CLOSED or the gh call fails, refuse to append the section + log to stderr; the orchestrator should treat this as a bounce.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- [ ] Bot refuses to append a PR-body section for issues that are already CLOSED at success time.\n- [ ] Bot refuses to append a PR-body section for issues from a different repo.\n- [ ] Regression test covers both failure modes.\n\n## Surfaced by\n\nPR #17 static review (R4 closeout, finding J-4).\n\n## Originally filed on\n\nConcaveTrillion/pd-book-tools#44 — closed there (wrong repo for workspace-tooling bugs).",
